{{Multiple issues| {{refimprove |date=April 2016}} {{example farm |date=March 2010}} }} {{Infobox number | number = 87 | divisor = 1, 3, 29, 87
}} '''87''' ('''eighty-seven''') is the [[natural number]] following [[86 (number)|86]] and preceding [[88 (number)|88]].
==In mathematics== '''87''' is:
* the sum of the squares of the first four primes (87 = 2<sup>2</sup> + 3<sup>2</sup> + 5<sup>2</sup> + 7<sup>2</sup>). * the sum of the sums of the divisors of the first 10 [[positive integers]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|1=A024916|2=sum_{k=1..n} sigma(k) where sigma(n) = sum of divisors of n}}</ref> * the twenty-sixth distinct [[semiprime]] and the eighth of the form (3.q). * 5! - 4! - 3! - 2! - 1! = 87
==In sports== * [[Cricket]] [[Cricket in Australia|in Australia]] holds 87 as a superstitiously unlucky score and is referred to as "the devil's number." This originates from the fact that 87 is [[13 (number)|13]] runs short of a [[Century (cricket)|century]]. 187, 287 and so on are also considered unlucky but is not as common as 87 on its own. * In the [[National Hockey League]], [[Wayne Gretzky]] scored a league-high 87 goals with the [[Edmonton Oilers]] in the [[1983–84 NHL season]].
==In other fields== '''Eighty-seven''' is also:
*The [[atomic number]] of [[francium]] *An answer to a popular puzzle question states 16, 06, 68, 88, xx, 98. The answer is 87 when looked upside down. *The number of years between the signing of the [[U.S. Declaration of Independence]] and the [[Battle of Gettysburg]], immortalized in [[Abraham Lincoln]]'s [[Gettysburg Address]] with the phrase "''[[Eighty|fourscore]]'' and seven years ago..." *The model number of [[Junkers Ju 87]] *The number of the French department [[Haute-Vienne]] *The [[code for international direct dial]] phone calls to [[Inmarsat]] and other services *The 87 [[filter (photography)|photographic filter]] blocks visible light allowing only infrared light to pass *The [[ISBN]] Group Identifier for books published in Denmark. *The opus number of the [[24 Preludes and Fugues (Shostakovich)|24 Preludes and Fugues]] of [[Dmitri Shostakovich]]. *In [[model railroading]], the ratio of the popular [[H0 scale]] is 1:87. [[Proto:87]] scale claims to offer precise proportions of wheels and tracks of real railroads. *[[David Bowie]] CD (1987) ''[[Never Let Me Down]]'' includes the song, "[['87 and Cry]]" *The [[87th United States Congress]] met from January 3, 1961 - January 3, 1963, during John F. Kennedy's time in office *[[Ed McBain]]'s ''[[87th Precinct]]: Lightning'' film starred [[Randy Quaid]] (1995) *87 punch includes one bottle of [[Bacardi]] rum (eight years aged) and [[7-up]] (two-liter bottle) *[[Wenger]] [[Swiss Army Knife]] version XXL, listed in the ''[[Guinness Book of World Records]]'' as the world's most multi-functional [[penknife]] with 87 tools *''[[Sonnet 87]]'' by [[William Shakespeare]] *Vault 87 is a main location in the game ''[[Fallout 3]]''
