'''Nominal techniques''' are a range of techniques, based on [[nominal sets]], for handling names and binding, e.g. in [[abstract syntax]]. Research into nominal sets gave rise to [[Nominal terms (computer science)|nominal terms]], a metalanguage for embedding object languages with name binding constructs.
